<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>FlashProxy Status — Past Incidents</title>
  <meta name="description" content="History of FlashProxy proxy downtime and degradation incidents — detected automatically by an open-source prober and committed to a public, tamper-evident integrity ledger." />
  <link rel="canonical" href="{{.SiteURL}}/incidents" />
  <meta name="robots" content="index,follow,max-image-preview:large" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#0d1117" />
  <link rel="icon" href="favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="FlashProxy Status" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="FlashProxy Status — Past Incidents" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="History of FlashProxy downtime and degradation incidents, independently verifiable." />
  <meta property="og:url" content="{{.SiteURL}}/incidents" />
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
  <meta name="twitter:title" content="FlashProxy — Past Incidents" />
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Proxy downtime &amp; degradation history, independently verifiable." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
  <script type="application/ld+json">{{.JSONLD}}</script>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="head">
      <div class="brand">flashproxy<span class="slash">/</span>status</div>
      <div class="updated">{{.Updated}}</div>
    </header>

    <nav class="subnav"><a href="/">&larr; Live status</a> &middot; <a href="/sla">100% Uptime SLA</a></nav>

    <section class="intro">
      <h1>Past Incidents</h1>
      <p>Every downtime and degradation episode FlashProxy has recorded, newest first. Each is detected automatically by the open-source prober — a product is marked <strong>Down</strong> only when every vantage point fails the same minute, and <strong>Degraded</strong> when its best-vantage response time stays above the SLA threshold for five consecutive minutes. Every event is committed to a public, signed, hash-chained <a href="/api/ledger">integrity ledger</a>, so this history is tamper-evident and independently verifiable.</p>
    </section>

    {{if .Incidents}}
    <section class="incidents">
      {{range .Incidents}}
      <div class="inc" data-status="{{.Severity}}">
        <div class="inc-top">
          <span class="inc-pkg">{{.Package}}</span>
          <span class="comp-stat" data-status="{{.Severity}}">{{.SeverityLabel}}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="inc-bot">
          <span class="inc-when">{{.Start}} &rarr; {{.End}}</span>
          <span class="inc-dur">{{if .Ongoing}}ongoing &middot; {{end}}{{.Duration}}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      {{end}}
    </section>
    <p class="inc-note">{{.Total}} incident{{if ne .Total 1}}s{{end}} on record &middot; events retained for {{.WindowDays}} days &middot; raw feed at <a href="/api/events">/api/events</a>.</p>
    {{else}}
    <div class="banner" data-status="operational">
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span class="banner-text">No incidents on record — 100% availability across the retained window.</span>
    </div>
    {{end}}

    <footer class="foot">
      synthetic probes &middot; <a href="/sla" class="plain">100% Uptime SLA</a> &middot;
      <a href="/api/events">events API</a> &middot;
      <a href="https://github.com/thealonlevi/flashproxy-sla">source</a>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
